            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-10T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.51/4–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-10T15:00:00-04:00">April 10, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. From Rockefeller.<note n="19" xml:id="d733fn19">Nelson A. Rockefeller,
                        Assistant Secretary of State for American Republic. Affairs.</note> Reurlet
                    March 27.<note n="20" xml:id="d733fn20">Not printed.</note> Nature of Fernando
                    Soto Harrison’s mission was to ascertain informally position of this Government
                    toward extension of present credit<note n="21" xml:id="d733fn21">The $2,000,000
                        loan of July 9, 1942.</note> and additional 3 million dollars making total
                    of 5 million dollars with extension of payment date of original loan for a
                    longer period. We will try to work out some satisfactory solution that will help
                    him meet his problem. In view of presence of Finance Minister at San Francisco
                        Conference,<note n="22" xml:id="d733fn22">United Nations Conference on
                        International Organization, San Francisco, California, April 25–June 26,
                        1945. For documentation concerning this Conference, see <ref target="frus1945v01#pg_1">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 1</ref>
                        ff.</note> this subject might well be discussed with Costa Rican Minister of
                    Finance and with appropriate officials of this Government at San Francisco.
                    [Rockefeller.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
